Making Liposomal Vitamin C: a tutorial 
	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DuZcOMhQehk

This method doesn’t require any lab gear or science background just some basic kitchen-adjacent equipment and a bit of attention to temperature.

Here’s the simplified version (1 month supply, ~30 doses of 1000mg each):
	1. Heat 150ml of distilled water to 60°C
	2. Stir in 24g of ascorbic acid + 6g of sodium ascorbate until fully dissolved
	3. Add 30ml vegetable glycerin and a few drops of orange oil (optional but makes it taste good)
	4. Slowly stir in 60g of liquid sunflower lecithin - I use a magnetic stirrer hotplate
	5. Stir at ~60°C for about 45–60 minutes
	6. Once done, top up with water to make 300ml total
	7. Let it cool, bottle it, refrigerate
	8.Take 10ml per day for 1000mg of liposomal vitamin C

